CAPE TOWN - The wildest place in Africa and home of dreams to many, Ratanga Junction has announced this festive season will be its last. The amusement park, in Cape Town, will close its doors in May next year after 19 years in operation. READ:Â World's largest indoor theme park set to open in Dubai Ratanga will be open throughout December and will hold a special New Year's celebration that will also serve as its farewell party. So much fun in Cape Town. #ratangajunction pic.twitter.com/fHRA8PCnUk Rides will not be operational during the party and no under 21s will be allowed entry. There will be no fireworks to say goodbye to The Cobra, The Slingshot,and Monkey Falls due to the proximity of the Intaka Island Reserve and surrounding residential areas. eNCA